$ $ORACLE_HOME/install/utl/rootmacro.sh

`$ORACLE_HOME/install/utl/rootmacro.sh` is called by `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/root_sh`.


Parameters that can be specified when `$ORACLE_HOME/install/utl/rootmacro.sh` is called are:
table { ll
  `-silent` ☰ But see also the environment variable `OUI_SILENT`
  `-crshome` ☰
  `-bindir` ☰ Sets and exports the variable `LBIN`. The three executables → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/bin/dbhome[`dbhome`], `oraenv` and `coraenv` (all located under `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/bin`) will be copied to the directory pointed at with `LBIN` (typically `→ Linux/fhs/usr/local/bin`).
  `-stdout` ☰ Enables stdout. But see also the environment variable `OUI_STDOUT`
  `-installTFA` ☰ *deprecated*
table }

Log messages are written to the file specified with the environment variable `LOG` if set or `→ Linux/fhs/dev/null` otherwise.
